\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8083487 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920 I am sorry you have been confused and frustrated. I hope that I will not continue your predicament. I am a simple and direct guy, so I have confidence things will turn out well for you. 
\par 
\par You say you are the beginner of the group. Keep thinking that. We are all beginners. 
\par 
\par Your story about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8083487 ...}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920  is touching, and happy and sad. Pray for her every day. We pray for the dead, because nobody is dead in God's eyes (our Lord said: "}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920\charrsid3888920  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920 God is the God of the living, and not of the dead}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920\charrsid13641497 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920 ", ) and because of love. Love never forgets. Some people are hung up about prayer for the dead, but there is no n
eed to be. We love and therefore we remember and pray. We pray with love and expectation. God knows all things and we do not know much. He has revealed very little to us about the state of our soul in the interim period between the death of the body and t
he reintegration of the soul with the body at the end of the age. the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5772602 Orthodox}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920  way is to not over analyze, but to pray! 
\par 
\par Here is a good prayer to say for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8083487 ...}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3888920  every day. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14560928 
