\par I like the message you say you have heard Jesus }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10302380 tell you for 5 years}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5772602 
: "Be still".  That is the key to our progress, for our passions to be still and to know God . This is a long road, b
ut God will never abandon us. He tells us plainly that His yoke is easy and His burner is light. therefore, when things are hard, we are doing something wrong! 
\par 
\par By "things are hard", I do not mean the circumstances of our life: whether we are poor or rich
, alone or in a family, free or in prison, sick or well. The circumstances of life are often hard, but the hardest things to endure is when our mind is not quiet, and filled with passions: anxiety, hate, lust, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7351568 judging, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5772602 remorse, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7351568 impatience, pride and vanity, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5772602 
loneliness. When we feel these things, we are not experiencing the easy yoke of Christ. When this happens, we must struggle to have quiet and intense prayer. I sent you some things about the Jesus prayer. this is the best thing, and also the Psalter. If 
we read the Gospel with expectation, the Holy Spirit will help us to change the way we think, how we look at things, and our priorities. We will }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7351568 become more peaceful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3888920 
